# Process types for the Jobora backend.
#
# Railway uses railway.json (Dockerfile build) for the web service and a per-
# service start command for the worker; this Procfile documents both process
# types and also works for Procfile-based hosts (Render workers, Heroku).
#
# web    — runs DB migrations (alembic upgrade head) then uvicorn on $PORT.
# worker — RQ worker consuming the "submissions" queue (no migrations; the web
#          process owns migrations to avoid races). Only needed when REDIS_URL is
#          set and you want submissions processed out-of-process (recommended at
#          scale; the API runs an in-process worker by default for low volume).
web: ./entrypoint.sh
worker: rq worker submissions --url $REDIS_URL
